---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Zakat Guide"
  subtitle="A comprehensive walkthrough of everything you need to know about Zakat — from foundational principles to modern asset classes."
>
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <!-- Intro -->
    <section>
      <p class="drop-cap text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-light">
        This guide is adapted from <em>Simple Zakat Guide: Understand and
        Calculate Your Zakat</em> by Joe Bradford (3rd Edition, 2022). It is
        organized as an interactive workbook designed to help you understand
        your Zakat obligations and compute exactly what you owe. The guide
        covers traditional assets like cash, gold, and silver, as well as
        modern instruments including cryptocurrency, NFTs, retirement accounts,
        and more.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-gold"></div>

    <!-- How This Guide Works -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-6">How This Guide Works</h2>
      <div class="card-gold mb-6">
        <p class="text-ink-light">
          The original book uses an interactive worksheet-based approach. Each
          chapter builds toward a final calculation. As you read, you will
          encounter references to specific worksheet line items (e.g.,
          <strong>Item 2a</strong>, <strong>Item 4g</strong>) which correspond
          to entries in the calculator. When you are ready, head to the
          <a href="/calculator" class="text-forest-500 underline decoration-gold/40 underline-offset-2 hover:text-forest-700 transition-colors">Calculator</a>
          to put your knowledge into practice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-3xl text-gold mb-2">4</div>
          <div class="font-ui text-sm text-ink-light font-medium">Worksheets</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-3xl text-gold mb-2">20+</div>
          <div class="font-ui text-sm text-ink-light font-medium">Asset Line Items</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-3xl text-gold mb-2">8</div>
          <div class="font-ui text-sm text-ink-light font-medium">Recipient Categories</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-3xl text-gold mb-2">2.5%</div>
          <div class="font-ui text-sm text-ink-light font-medium">Flat Zakat Rate</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-gold"></div>

    <!-- Table of Contents -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-8">Guide Contents</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Part 1 -->
        <div class="card hover:border-gold/40 transition-all duration-300">
          <a href="/guide/principles" class="block group">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-display text-sm text-gold font-bold tracking-wider uppercase mt-1">Part One</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-gold transition-colors">
                  Introductory Principles
                </h3>
                <p class="text-ink-light mb-3">
                  Foundational concepts of Islamic financial ethics and essential
                  Zakat terminology.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light space-y-1.5">
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold/50"></span>
                    Chapter I — Principles of Islamic Financial Ethics
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold/50"></span>
                    Chapter II — Basic Terms and Concepts
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Part 2 -->
        <div class="card hover:border-gold/40 transition-all duration-300">
          <a href="/guide/assets" class="block group">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-display text-sm text-gold font-bold tracking-wider uppercase mt-1">Part Two</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-gold transition-colors">
                  Assets, Earnings &amp; Expenses
                </h3>
                <p class="text-ink-light mb-3">
                  Detailed breakdown of every asset type subject to Zakat, plus
                  deductible expenses.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light space-y-1.5">
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold/50"></span>
                    Chapter III — Assets (Cash, Gold, Stocks, Crypto, Real Estate…)
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold/50"></span>
                    Chapter IV — Haram Earnings
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold/50"></span>
                    Chapter V — Expenses and Liabilities
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Part 3 -->
        <div class="card hover:border-gold/40 transition-all duration-300">
          <a href="/guide/giving" class="block group">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-display text-sm text-gold font-bold tracking-wider uppercase mt-1">Part Three</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-gold transition-colors">
                  Who to Give To &amp; When to Give
                </h3>
                <p class="text-ink-light mb-3">
                  Understanding the eight Quranic categories of recipients,
                  ineligible parties, and distribution guidelines.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light space-y-1.5">
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold/50"></span>
                    Chapter VI — Giving Zakat
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Calculator -->
        <div class="card border-l-4 border-l-gold hover:border-gold/40 transition-all duration-300">
          <a href="/calculator" class="block group">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-display text-sm text-gold font-bold tracking-wider uppercase mt-1">Tool</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-gold transition-colors">
                  Zakat Calculator
                </h3>
                <p class="text-ink-light">
                  An interactive, step-by-step calculator with all four
                  worksheets. Compute your Nisab, list your assets, deduct
                  expenses, and determine your Zakat obligation.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-gold"></div>

    <!-- Important Note -->
    <section>
      <div class="card bg-forest-50/50 border-forest-200/50">
        <h3 class="text-lg mb-3 text-forest-700">A Note on Scholarly Guidance</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
          This guide presents one scholarly approach to Zakat calculation. Islamic
          jurisprudence includes diverse valid opinions on many of these topics.
          For specific rulings about your personal situation, always consult a
          qualified Islamic scholar or your local imam. This resource is meant to
          educate and provide a practical framework, not to replace personalized
          scholarly advice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</GuideLayout>
